{"tid":2210574,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"美國法院暫停WeChat上架禁令","createTime":"2020-09-20T13:32:33.000Z","updateTime":"2020-09-20T23:31:26.000Z","uid":10199,"like":9,"dislike":49,"uniUserReply":57,"replies":[{"pid":"69d45d1e3719eabb3a1988ee7e7673662cf74fc0","tid":2210574,"uid":10199,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-09-20T13:32:33.000Z","msg":"Judge halts Trump administration order banning WeChat from app stores<br />\n<br />\nPUBLISHED SUN, SEP 20 20209:28 AM EDT<br />\n A U.S. judge early Sunday blocked the Commerce Department from requiring Apple and Alphabet  Google to remove Tencent Holding&rsquo;s WeChat for downloads by late Sunday.<br />\n<br />\nU.S. Magistrate Judge Laurel Beeler in California said in an order that WeChat users who filed a lawsuit &ldquo;have shown serious questions going to the merits of the First Amendment claim, the balance of hardships tips in the plaintiffs favor.&ldquo;<br />\n<br />\nBeeler&rsquo;s preliminary injunction also blocked the Commerce order that would have barred other transactions with WeChat in the United States that could have degraded the site&rsquo;s usability for current U.S. users. The U.S. Commerce Department did not immediately comment."},{"pid":"e6253bc193f6d522498d8914f13218e045c06867","tid":2210574,"uid":62226,"like":8,"dislike":8,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-09-20T13:35:43.000Z","msg":"美國法官肯定收咗中共錢<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/knife.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"6a98d40cb656c0965f708d9e3d551a8246f6d3e3","tid":2210574,"uid":22556,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-20T13:36:52.000Z","msg":"下架？"},{"pid":"c346ca9bac4367a67e4d94c604b46f3fa19a2516","tid":2210574,"uid":286897,"like":4,"dislike":1,"score":3,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-09-20T13:38:13.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"9b888b0b15b3f646ede04bd86a0065bce44b911a","tid":2210574,"uid":263150,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"quote":